a:5:{s:5:"title";s:80:"Close introduces ‘Close Forms,’ a native web form builder for lead capture";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:1105:"<p>Close added a built-in forms product called Close Forms, now available to customers across all plans.</p>
<h3>What’s new</h3>
<p>Close Forms lets teams create and embed website forms that send submissions straight into Close—without external automation tools.</p>
<p>Key capabilities</p>
<ul>
<li>Drag-and-drop form builder (no coding)</li>
<li>Website embedding for real-time lead capture</li>
<li>Automatic routing into Close with structured CRM data</li>
<li>Built-in spam protection</li>
<li>Form activity visible on the lead record</li>
<li>Smart Views to filter/search form submissions</li>
<li>Notifications when new leads arrive</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>This reduces setup and tool dependency for teams that previously relied on third-party form tools or Zapier-style routing. For sales teams, it shortens the path from website submission to follow-up.</p>
<h3>How to access</h3>
<p>In Close: Settings → Forms to create a new form.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://www.close.com/changelog/web-forms">https://www.close.com/changelog/web-forms</a></p>
